description: At least 35 people were killed and dozens more injured in an Israeli airstrike on an encampment in Rafah. As bird flu spreads among dairy cattle herds, raw milk is undergoing renewed scrutiny.
title: Israeli airstrike kills dozens in Rafah; raw milk under scrutiny

description: The Israeli military said it killed two Hamas militant leaders in the strike but Palestinian health officials say dozens of  civilians who had sought shelter in an encampment were killed and injured.
title: An Israeli airstrike killed 35 Palestinians in an encampment for displaced people

description: The government figure is roughly triple the U.N. estimate of victims killed in the South Pacific island nation's interior. Estimates of the casualties have varied widely since the disaster occurred.
title: Papua New Guinea tells the U.N. that a landslide buried more than 2,000 people

description: Former U.S. Attorney Harry Litman breaks down three broad possible conclusions the jury could reach.
title: The 3 ways Trump's hush money trial could end, as jury deliberations begin soon

description: Russia's war in Ukraine is deepening divisions across Europe. One example is the Baltic nation of Latvia, formerly part of the Soviet Union. One third of those living in Latvia are Russian speaking and now some elderly residents, who may have lived there for decades, are being forced to prove their loyalty or leave.
title: Questions of Loyalty in Latvia
